social_posts.post_text:
The most lovely dinner at @liftbarandgrill 🥰 We've passed by so many times on our seawall walks and finally had the opportunity to try their food. Out of everything we tried, the raw oysters, sablefish, and sourdough (with butter) was our favourite 🤤 Can't wait to enjoy the view during the day time on our next visit.

Thanks for having us, Lift Bar and Grill ❤️

Hard to believe my week in LA is over 😪😫 Enjoyed the sun and some time off posting food content. Looking forward to when we can have @marugame_ in Canada 🇨🇦🍜

Taste of LA 🇺🇸 More photos from our trip! It was my husband's first time in California so of course we had to hit up In-N-Out and do up our burgers animal style 🍔 After having it multiple times myself...I'm still team Shake Shack 😛 What about you?

Taste of LA 🇺🇸 Went to the famous @parksbbq and really enjoyed ourselves! The meat is high quality and there were a variety of side dishes you don't often get in Vancouver. It's definitely pricier than some other local spots. The worst part? That dang exchange rate 💰🫠
Taste of LA 🇺🇸 I could use one of these breakfast sandwiches right about now 🥹 So much fun sitting at the counter and watching the crew make the eggs. Fluffy perfection as expected 💖

Ok, fine, it was my view from yesterday 🙃 checked out @toasttocoastbrunch with a couple of foodie friends and I'm so glad there is now another brunch spot in Richmond! Their Korean fusion menu is fun twist on classic brunch dishes. I got the Fisherman's Feast with Sweet Korean Beef. Loved with sourdough toast with jam and the hashbrown blocks. Can't wait to come back again! Note: Walk-ins only on weekends and space is limited 😬

Kimchi Cafe 😍 Bookmark this Korean restaurant in Vancoucer for the next time you need something warm...which is right about now 😅 Love the simple yet thoughtful menu of traditional Korean and also fusion dishes. Out of everything we tried, I most enjoyed the @oiso150 ramyun and the seafood waffle 🧇 The drinks are on point as well👌

Thanks for hosting us, OiSO! We will be back!

location.city_name: Sofitel Los Angeles at Beverly Hills

social_posts.post_text: When people ask me what my favourite meal in LA 🇺🇸 was...eating tacos from the Taqueria Dolores tent outside my hotel 🌮

$99.95 hot pot set for 4 people 😍 at @liuyishou.vancouver Burnaby location. A great deal for the variety of dishes you get (see last slide). We added a few additional items like quail eggs, sticky rice cakes, and pork belly. Sauce bar and broth not included.
Merry Christmas and Happy Holidays 🥰 A very full feast with my family last night 🎄🎅 My niece admiring my cheese platter 😉

Bookmark this spot if you love katsu 🥰 @katsusan_van serves perfectly fried and breaded katsu in Richmond! Their sets come with a variety of sauces, seasoning, and also free refills on rice, miso soup, and salad. My personal favourite is the chicken katsu. Recommend ordering a side of their curry to have with rice or use as a dip 🤤

Thanks for having us, Katsu San!

The flu bug has finally hit me 🫠 so no fun eats this week but here are some photos from my experience at the famous Jitlada Thai Restaurant in LA 🇺🇸 😆 Overall I found  our dinner just OK (maybe too much hype on the internet). We lucked out and only waited 10 minutes for a table. The standout dish for me was the crab fried rice which had an abundance of meat on top. I found the pad see ew too sweet for my liking and the fried rolls were just ok. The tom yum soup was good with a spicy kick 🔥 Spent around $100 CAD for the food featured.
The best kinda gifts are edible 😉 For Christmas this year, I made my first batch of chili oil to share with friends ☺️ Not too shabby but definitely looking forward to tweaking my recipe/technique 📝
Best way to close out 2022 🥰 almost fully home cooked meal by my mom 👩‍🍳 Happy New Year!

An underrated spot for pho 🤤 I love how clean and light the broth is at @vietmamacafe 🍜 It's not too salty and doesn't leave you thirsty after. It's a big bowl of pho for $13.50. Highly recommend adding a spring roll to make it a combo for $15.50✌️

I tried something new with my soup 😦 Ever since I saw @luckyironfish pop up on my feed, I've been curious to try! If you haven't heard of it before, Lucky Iron Fish is an easy way to add iron to your food. Just add it to 4 cups of boiling liquid (soup, sauce, or any liquid-based dish) for 10 minutes and add 2 drops of acidity (like lemon juice). This will add 6-8mg of tasteless iron that is easy to absorb.

You can't use it while pressure cooking but I  simmered my soup for a bit longer afterward and added it in then👌 Will post a link in my stories in case you're interested in trying!

#luckyironcrew #luckyironfish #irondeficiency #ironsupplement #creatorco @creator.co.community

Literally the king of all mochi in size and taste 🤤 The mango mochi hype at @riceholicvancouver is real 🥭 I love how fragrant the mochi skin is and the fruit is also super fresh. Make sure you check their IG page for when they have it available and pre-order to avoid disappointment!

How to serve Lunar New Year dinner in 25 minutes 🤭 @abento_official has made hosting and gift giving easier for Chinese New Year by offering three different gift boxes. I was given the Gift Box C to share with my parents which included four dishes: Buddha Jumps Over the Wall, Braised Pork Hock, Sesame Oil Chicken Sticky Rice, and Braised "Lion Head". All come frozen and easy to reheat by simmering in hot water.

Pre-order and pick up between now and January 23👌

Still dreaming about the Primo Marge Pizza 🍕 from @gastronomygastown 🤤 This new restaurant just opened and their concept is fusing a modern day Vancouver with Italian influence. The space is beautiful and cozy. They even have the wood fire oven going! Highlights of my meal included the pizza (amazing crust) and all the appetizers 🥹🤤 The Elvis, a banana Panna Cotta, had everything I want for my dream dessert. I am looking forward to coming back with my family!

Congratulations on your opening, Gastronomy Gastown! And thank you for the invite✨️
Tag a cheeseburger loving friend! A smashing good date night at @between2bunsburgers 😍🍔 Between two soft, sweet buns are fresh patties and gooey cheese. Have you been here? 👀

Finally made it out to this famous Vancouver restaurant...@zarakvancouver 🙃 A lovely evening celebrating two of my friends and their birthdays! The highlight of the meal for me were the mantu (dumplings) and the soft paneer cheese with sourdough👌 If you haven't checked out their sister restaurant, @eatdrinkafghan 👀 you should!

Bookmark this Vancouver food truck if you love eggs or just darn good sandwiches 🥪🍳 Checked out @crackonvan and they did not disappoint! Highly recommend trying their Crack Sandwich and soon-to-be-released Kickin Chicken 🤤 High quality meats, eggs, and sourdough bread. Also their hashbrowns are to die for. Can't go wrong!

Thanks for inviting us to try your bomb sandwiches, Crack On! 💣

This weather has me craving claypot rice, also known as bo jai faan [煲仔飯] 🤤 Not many places make it in Vancouver but it's such a comfort food of mine. The rice, meats, and veggies are all cooked in a claypot over fire. Usually the rice on the bottom crisps up 😍 Love the sweet hospitality at @41noodlericepothouse and how homecooked their food tastes.

Good deal alert 🔥🔥🔥 From Jan 20 to Feb 5, visit @eatdundas for their $25 pp Dine Out Menu 😌

Spring Roll (vegan option available)
Papaya Salad 
Choice of Noodle Soup (Vegan option available)
Deep fried banana or Mango Sticky Rice 

I personally loved the spring roll, great flavour and crispy/fresh. Papaya Salad was so refreshing as well. My husband enjoyed his Bun Bo Hue and they even have a vegan version. Of course, we had to add some Vietnamese Iced Coffee too 🙃

Thanks for having us, @eatdundas 🙏
Happy Lunar New Year to all that celebrate 🙂🐰 A delicious meal cooked by my mom tonight. Followed up with mochi and trying those gigantic blueberries that have been popping up everywhere!🧧

Still dreaming of these tacos 🌮 A few of you DM'd and recommended this spot. Y'all were not kidding when you said @taqueriaplayatropical has some of the best Mexican food 😍 Stuffed tacos from $2.50-$3, fresh guacamole and delicious cocktails/drinks. Definitely bookmarked and coming back!
Can you do it too?! A skill I wish I had was pan flipping 😆 A behind the scenes of my mom whipping up Lunar New Year dinner, including a blooper of her veggie flip fail 🥸

A brand new location opening soon for this popular hot pot spot 🤩 D from the TOV team was invited to check out the new @thedolarshopcanada location on Kingsway and it was gorgeous inside! Same great food and service 👌
Stopped by this Japanese grocery store in Richmond the other day to pick up lunch 😍 Love browsing all the goodies at @izumiya_market

Seafood lovers listen up! It's the final week of @dineoutvanfest which means it's your last chance to get the $50pp build-your-own board at @smittysoysterhouse.on.main 🥺 Choose two items to go along with their chowder and get either creme brulee or chocolate mouse for dessert. My personal picks would be their Halibut Fritters and Wolf Candy (lamb) 😍 Don't forget to add a side of fresh oysters 🦪

Thanks for having us, Smitty's! Can't wait to visit again for happy hour 🍻
How do you like to eat your mazesoba? With vinegar or no vinegar? Rice at the end? 🤤

Multi-course Japanese Kaiseki Dinner Set Menu 😍 @hoshi.japanese.cuisine_ is raising the bar for their Valentine's Day dinner created by Chef Senn. The Matsu Set starts at $238 pp and the Take Set (premium) is $318 pp. Definitely a treat for a special day and there were a number of bites that had me 🤤 Like the A5 Wagyu and Chutoro with Uni. A few of the ingredients and fish are flown in from Japan ❤️👌 Head over to their website for the full menu!

Thank you for having me, Hoshi! What a special meal.

location.city_name: Ban Chok Dee Thai Cuisine - Langley

social_posts.post_text:
I had super high expectations visiting this Thai restaurant in Langley 😅 Mostly from social media and also the raving Google reviews. Overall I had a good experience but I wouldn't say the food was mind blowing. The service was friendly and it was bumping on a Saturday night. Appetizer platter was a great way to share a bit of everything and perhaps the best part of the meal for me. The Pad See Ew and Pad Thai flavour wise was OK but both were missing that "breath of wok" or heat from the wok that I was anticipating. Portions are HUGE and suitable for sharing.

Have you been here before? What was your experience like?

Just need a little something before we went out for the evening 🍜 Got the House Special Spicy Sate Pho thinking it would be a peanut broth but it was more like their usual broth with chili oil 😅 Overall, not bad not bad...a decent option for the area. Cash only.

Does anyone know if this is related to Gold Train on Kingsway? 🤔

Do you enjoy dining solo? 🙃 I had a night to myself in Calgary so I wandered over to check out @tenfoothenry which has earned a spot on Canada’s Top 100. They're a share plates restaurant but I was pleased to find out they also offer partial plates for certain dishes too!

I had the cauliflower that was topped with a scallion ginger sauce and flavoured with gochujang and sesame. I also had their spaghetti cacio e pepe. And their red prawns with grilled corn and cashew salsa macha. 

Loved the bites I had and the creative flair on ingredients/pairings. The service was top notch. They comp'd my spaghetti because there was a mix up 🥹 My only wish was that I had someone to share with because the flavours can be quite bold and rich. Overall, a lovely experience 😊

Always super impressed with the food scene in Calgary 😍 Visited @themajortombar which is situated on the 40th floor in a commercial building downtown. Had to have Alberta beef in some way shape or form on this trip and it hit the spot. I was also told the potato donuts were to die for and they delivered👌

A feast for seafood lovers 😍 Head over to your local @thecaptainsboil with your loved ones or special someone to enjoy their Romantic Feast from now until February 14. We went with their "I Like You" feast which includes everything you see in the reel: snow crab legs, mussels, clams, sausage, corn, potato, oysters, and fried rice. Parts of this feast is customizable too 🙃 

Thank you, Captain's Boil, for this treat 🙌

OKKKK I see you @_burgercrush 🍔 Visited with a few colleagues last week and I enjoyed the experience from the burgers to the 90s music 🤭 Loved the soft bun and patty. Will be back to try the shakes since they're dangerously close to work 👀

Finally tried this little local gem in Richmond! @shoestringcafe is tucked away in the commercial area of Richmond, serving everything from steaks to seafood to pasta. We visited for Valentine's Day and while the special set was pricey at $98...the value was definitely there. Chunks of seafood in the chowder, fresh bread, big portions of meat, and sizeable desserts to finish the meal. They ran out of prime rib so I ended up getting their ribeye which was on point 😌 My husband's lamb chops were good but not amazing. Overall, would come back again for a regular set menu 🙌

All my husband wanted for his birthday was some simple Cantonese dishes and a bucket of rice 🤣 love the service, taste, and portions at @shoomtime 🥰 We got fried squid, half a scallion chicken, stir fried veggies with preserved meat, lamb hot pot, and rice. Need to come back for their late night menu at 9pm!

Breakfast for $11 or less 👀 I've been seeing posts on FB and IG talking about this new Hong Kong style breakfast/noodle spot in the President Plaza food. I opted for the satay beef instant noodle set which came with scrambled eggs, toast, and milk tea. For those unfamiliar with HK style breakfast, this is a very typical combo. The best part of this meal was the silky eggs which paired nicely with the toast 🍳🍞 The noodles were just OK in my opinion, good flavour but a little soft. The milk tea was missing that aromatic tea flavour and mine was slightly bitter. Overall, I think it's a great value for $11 and I would get it again. But won't be rushing back because I hate how chaotic the plaza is 😅

Have you checked Cha Kee out?

BOGO 50% off Mazesoba and Ramen 😧🍜 @kokoro_mazesoba has a brand new River District location 🥹 They are currently doing a soft open but will be celebrating their grand opening on March 3 & 4 with a BOGO 50% off promotion on both days. Tag your noodle loving friends and save the date 😍

Congratulations and thanks for having us, Kokoro Mazesoba!

When your videos from dinner turn out grainy as heck 🙈 at least I got a decent one of the Eggplant Parm 🍆 which was one of the highlights from my meal at @straight_and_marrow 😍 The brisket is another must try!

What can $54.95 (+ tax) get you??? An entire bag of snacks from @hflvancouver snacks in the city! If you love trying new snacks, this one is perfect for you! I'm blown away by the number of goodies inside valued at over $150+. You also get access to their virtual event with giveaways and $10 off your next @londondrugs purchase of $50. No wonder they sold out 🫨 Keep an eye out for more events via their IG 👀

Thanks for the invite to check out the experience, HFL!

Do you set your tempura aside or leave it on top of the rice? 🤭🍤 My husband's first time at @kanekohannosuke.vancouver and my first visit to the @the.amazing.brentwood location. One thing we really enjoy about this tendon (tempura over rice) is actually the rice texture and the sauce👌 I always get the special assorted tendon but would be happy with just the ebi and egg over rice 🥹

Thanks for the lovely lunch, Kaneko Hannosuke!

10 minute lazy lunch courtesy of a can of spicy Korean tuna gifted to me from a friend 😜 this was so easy to make and so satisfying 😌 

Tuna, rice, fried egg, mayo, furikake, green onions and some seaweed if you prefer to wrap it all up!

Bookmark this spot next time you're in Richmond and in need of a protein smoothie 👀 @lifepluscanada is bringing the smoothie bar experience without the hefty downtown price tags. Drinks start from $5.99 and they even have milk tea flavour!

Thanks for inviting us to check out your drinks, Lifeplus Natural Health ❤️

After hearing about my coworkers rave about this little hole in the wall by our office, I finally checked it out 😍 Run by a friendly couple, @crossroads.cafe_van features sandwiches, soups, and daily specials. Their pierogies were so, so good. It was around $11...topped with caramelized onions and sour cream 🤤 I added an extra $2 for kolbassa (sausage) and it was perfection! Available on Wednesdays as their daily special.

Tip: Cash or etransfer only!
IYKYK 😍 I was shocked when my colleagues said they had never tried a @purdyschocolatier ice cream bar 😳 Friday afternoon treat with the office crew 😀

Noodles or rice?! What would you pick for your DIY bowl at @goodbowlofficial 👀 I had a fun time visiting with my parents. Bowls are customizable from the vegetables to the protein to the sauces. Impressed to see Beyond Meat as an option now too! 👏 Their juices and smoothies are made with fresh ingredients before your eyes as well 👌

Thanks for having us, Goodbowl!

How do you eat your tangsuyuk (Korean sweet & sour pork)? 🤭 Sauce on the side for me 🙋‍♀️ One of our favourite spots for Korean food. 

Have you been to Sumi before? ☺️

location.city_name: Hotpot Palace 御庭-精緻鍋物

social_posts.post_text:
Grab your hot pot buddy and head over to @hotpot_palace to try their new lunch special 😍 The sets start at $27.80 and are great value considering it comes with a plate of meat, choice of broth, unlimited sauce and snack bar, an assorted plate of veggies/sides, and unlimited rice and noodles. They also have add ons for extra meat and sashimi 🤤

Lunch specials are available Tuesday to Sunday.

Thanks for having us, Hot Pot Palace 💜

location.city_name: Sweet Memory Dessert 有香甜點輕食

social_posts.post_text:
Taiwanese dinner combo with rice bowl, side dishes, and dessert for $16.95 at @sweet_memory_dessert 🤤 I enjoyed the Turkey on Rice (a signature Taiwanese dish) and the silky smooth grass jelly. The appetizers consist of 3 small side dishes. 

What do you think of this deal? 🙃

Did I have prime rib by myself at this famous establishment? Why yes, I did! In San Francisco for a few days so I took myself on a solo date to check out @thehouseofprimerib 🥰 Usually they suggest making a reservation at least 6-8 weeks in advance. I was lucky to walk in right before dinner started and I got seated at the bar almost right away. The people behind me had a quote 1.5 hour wait 🫣 The prime rib was indeed worth the hype and I loved all the sides as well. Did you know some of the cuts also come with unlimited refills including meat?! 😳

San Francisco photo dump 📸 Back in Vancouver! While I had a limited time in SF, I was able to fit in some good eats. I may need salads this week 😅

*most restaurant handles are tagged in the photos incase you're interested ☺️

Still incredibly full from this generous meal from @dhaliwalslounge 😳 If you're looking for an Indian restaurant with fun cocktail, this is the place! We tried so many dishes but my favourites were: Signature Chop (lamb), Prawn Balcho, Pista & Coconut Crusted Salmon, and the Palak Paneer 🤤 Everything was excellent with rice and naan. The space was lovely and good for big groups.

Thank you to Dhaliwal's Lounge for hosting our group ❤️

Little hidden brunch spot 😎 if you're looking for a restaurant that takes reservation for brunch and is good for groups...I was pleasantly surprised by @socialyvr 🍳🥓 The menu isn't extensive but there is a little something for everyone. The upstairs space is quite beautiful with lots of natural light.

Have you tried these viral croissants? I'm late to the party but I finally had my first Supreme Croissant from @littlecafeonrobson 😍🥐 It's pretty amazing how they're able to shape it, maintain the layers and stuff it with filling. My favourite was definitely the Mont Blanc and the (kinda secret) savoury Supreme Sandwich 🥪 Some of their flavours rotate so be sure to check their IG for what's new!

Thank you for all the croissants, Little Cafe! My colleagues were very happy 🤣

Michelin recommended restaurant @newmandarinrestaurant has new dishes on the menu! Out of everything we tried, my favourite was the Teriyaki (more like motoyaki) Lobster, Taishan Goose with Five Flavours, Pan fried Wild Black Cod, and the Braised Scallop w/ Eggplant & Egg Tofu in Clay Pot. Of course we also had to have some of their signature BBQ Roast Pig 🤗

 Thank you to Chef @tonyzhang1222 for inviting us to try and @foodsnapsbyjess for arranging 👨‍🍳

One flight of stairs below on Richard's St is newly opened @dilliheights 🤗 They feature tasty Indian street food and serve up a mean cup of chai 😍 My husband and I tried a few of their dishes and would highly recommend: the steamed momo (dumpling skin is perfection), the chicken samosa chaat, and spicy chicken burger. Ps. The hot sauce that comes with the momo is 🔥 but also so good.

I learned two new things 😲 Number one - @tacofinolovesyou has a location on W Pender downtown called Oasis. And number two - they serve breakfast during the weekdays from 8 am to 11 am 🌮 Can confirm that breakfast tacos and burritos are just as good as their regular stuff 😉😜

Thanks for breakfast, Tacofino 🍳

My Dinner Club hit up @crabhotlau.vancouver for our March gathering 😍🦀 This little spot is known for their Vietnamese crab dishes and hot pot! We loved, loved, loved their square crab spring rolls which I highly recommend getting a platter so you get the noodles and veggies. The chicken wings were tasty as well! The Rice Field Crab Hot Pot Lau Cua Dong is full of flavour, featuring pork bone broth mixed with crab paste and fried pork fat. We got it with a side of pork jowl and sliced beef 🤩 To temper expectations, I wouldn't say the broth is packed with crab flavour but rather a subtle aroma of it. Overall, a very enjoyable meal and I look forward to coming back!

Ps. I love that JoJo's music is trending 🙃

It's been ages since I've visited @takeyasushi and they've transformed their next door space to all grab and go style 👀 so many choices but I ended grabbing a basic tuna mayo onigiri 🤭🍙 Have you stopped by?

Taste of Toronto 🇨🇦 Limited time to try food since I'm only in town for less than 48 hours 🥲 @paitoronto came highly recommended by friends and @simuliu lol, and I was not disappointed! I got the Pad See Ew with chicken, Moo Ping (pork skewers) and Thai Iced Tea. The noodles were perfectly stir fried and you can definitely feel the heat from the wok 👌 It's hard to find a good version of this dish in Vancouver (in my opinion). The Thai Iced Tea was spot on in strength, sweetness, and creaminess. The skewers are super flavorful and well charred. Unfortunately mine came undercooked but they quickly took care of it and also comp'd it on my final bill. I definitely want to come back and try their Pad Thai and Chicken Wings 😍

Have you visited here before?

Taste of New York 🇺🇸 Been a little MIA this week because of a work trip to the East Coast. After our big event, took my boss and colleague to @joespizzanyc 🍕 We had to wait for awhile 🙈 but it was worth it! Loved how it came piping hot, thin, and had ample toppings. The crust got a little hard at the end but overall a good NY experience!

Checked out the new @wa.curry downtown for lunch today and it was bumping! Order at the counter or on your phone and pick up at the counter. The curry was quite flavourful with minced bits of wagyu. It is on the salty side so I wish it came with more rice. I got a small with a pork katsu add on. The katsu was perfectly fried with light batter 👌

What's your go-to spot for Chinese BBQ? I personally love @chinatownbbq for the all around experience. Good bbq, clean, and super friendly service ☺️ The roast pig has crispy skin and the perfect fat ratio. We had to grab a side of their ginger scallion sauce too!

INSTANT NOODLE PARTY! 🍜 My friends and I got together to sample some of our favourite instant noodles. Super fun to try old and new ones 🙃 A few of you asked which ones I liked best...I personally enjoyed the Potato Noodle Soup (my regular go-to), the Angry Chapaguri and Samyang ❤️ Between 5 people we had 12 noodles...safe to say I need a break from ramen for awhile 😅

What is your fav?

TARO MOCHI FILLED BRIOCHE DONUTS 🍩 random stop at the @mellovancouver Arbutus location and they had these new donuts filled with taro cream and mini mochi 🤤 I said I'd save half but that didn't happen 🤣 only available until Easter Monday 😩

One of our favourite brunch spots is @jamcafeyvr 😍 I was really craving a Benny for some reason and loved the Fennel Pork Sausage Patty & Crispy Brussel Sprouts Benny they had on special. Lucked out and only waited around 25 mins on a long weekend 🍳🥓

Where do you like to brunch?

social_posts.post_text:
Finally tried this popular beef noodle soup spot! @unobeefnoodle specializes in this traditional Taiwanese dish 🍜 I'm not expert but I thought the bowls were pretty solid! I loved my chewy thick noodles while my husband opted for thin. My only note was that the broth was a little salty for my taste. Super flavourful otherwise. 

Thin vs. Thick. What would you choose?!

This may be my new go-to cake shop in Richmond! Got a first sneak peak of the new @daangocakelab and it was so good 😍 A variety of different flavours available for all palates. Definitely get a slice of cake when you're there and try their HK style milk tea. Can't wait to come back when they start serving gelato too! Check out their IG page for more info on the grand opening and exact address.

Authentic tacos 🌮 at home! My friend raved about the taco kit from @74c05_4u and she was not wrong 😍 I tried the Al Pastor tacos and they were soooo good..juicy, flavourful, and lots of meat! Everything comes frozen and just needs a quick reheat. $30 only which could probably feed a family of 4 or make for a few meals for 1-2 people. I can't wait to try their other kits!

#tacos #food #love #FoodPorn #local
It's always a good day with dim sum and friends...and smiley salted egg yolk buns 😌 Glad to see @sunsuiwah on Main St open for dim sum this morning despite the scary fire yesterday!

Chocolate Strawberry Bouquets 💐🍓 @lafraise.rose is offering these beautiful edible arrangements for Mother's Day but honestly they would be great for any special occasion 😍 Each bouquet comes with approximately 10 Belgian white chocolate strawberries and fresh seasonal flowers (valued at $139). A perfect gift for a loved one that enjoys sweets and florals 🥰 They also have products made by local companies available at their storefront.

Thank you for the beautiful gift that my friends devoured, La Fraise Rose 🌹

THAI X VIETNAMESE CUISINE 😍 @hpnoodlehouse serves a number of classic Asian dishes from Thai curry to Vietnamese pho. I was pleasantly surprised by a number of their dishes like Thai Red Curry, Mango Salad and also Special House Fried Rice which was loaded with toppings! The portions are HUGE and great for sharing. I loved my Vietnamese Iced Coffee and they even have some fun cocktails 🍸 The fried banana was 😌

Celebrated two Dinner Club birthdays at Michelin recommended Greek restaurant @nammosestiatorio 🇬🇷 First of all, the interior is beautifully decorated and the service is friendly. They recommend selecting a few items from the menu to share and I'm glad we went with 1-2 selections per person. It wasn't listed on their menu, but you can get a trio of their delicious dips for $20 and it comes with two servings of pita...highly recommend! The Kalamari was lightly battered and generously topped with red onions 🦑 For mains, we got the Arni Psito (lamb shoulder) and Moschari Youvetsi (short rib orzo). I thought both of them were just aight. Well-plated and big portions but a bit on the salty side for me. The Patates Fournou aka lemon roasted potatoes were very tangy and soft 🍋 For dessert, I loved the Ekmek which was light, fluffy and not too sweet.
